Name: ILO Working Papers
Description: The International Labour Organization (ILO) is devoted to promoting social justice 
 and internationally recognized human and labour rights, pursuing its founding mission that 
 labour peace is essential to prosperity. Today, the ILO helps advance the creation of decent 
 work and the economic and working conditions that give working people and business people a 
 stake in lasting peace, prosperity and progress. Its main aims are to promote rights at 
 work, encourage decent employment opportunities, enhance social protection and strengthen 
 dialogue on work-related issues. Working papers published by the ILO cover a wide range 
 of topics related to the world of work and social justice.
